From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: fs: un-static do_sys_openat2 for built-in callers

KACS's kacs_open syscall needs do_sys_openat2 to perform a full
VFS open from a userspace path + open_how. Remove static and add
a declaration to fs/internal.h so built-in subsystems can call it
with compile-time signature checking.

--- a/fs/open.c
+++ b/fs/open.c
@@ -1422,3 +1422,3 @@

-static int do_sys_openat2(int dfd, const char __user *filename,
+int do_sys_openat2(int dfd, const char __user *filename,
 			  struct open_how *how)
--- a/fs/internal.h
+++ b/fs/internal.h
@@ -361,2 +361,4 @@
 void pidfs_get_root(struct path *path);
 void nsfs_get_root(struct path *path);
+
+int do_sys_openat2(int dfd, const char __user *filename, struct open_how *how);
